title: Huge ‘rock’ on frozen lake turns out to be animal desperate for help; video
text:
Huge ‘rock’ on frozen lake turns out to be animal desperate for help; video 
February 03, 2017 By David Strege 
In the distance, Viktor Johannessen and Sigrid Sjösteen spotted what they thought to be a huge rock on the ice of the frozen lake in northern Sweden. 
“We had just finished our lunch,” Johannessen told LiveLeak . “We looked out the window and saw that the ice looked strange a few hundred meters from the shore. 
RELATED: Two fighting bull moose become frozen in time — literally 
“About seven meters from a small island across the bay, it looked like someone had thrown a huge rock onto the ice, but through the binoculars we could see that the ‘rock’ really was a moose struggling to get out of the water. It was evident that it was having problems.” 
So the two grabbed some tools, put on their ice skates and went to help the animal. 
Using an axe, the rescuers chiseled out a route to the shoreline and directed the poor moose in that direction. After a little bit of a struggle, it finally found its bearings and took off into the woods.
